National treasury cabinet secretary Ukur Yatani on Thursday unveiled an ambitious ksh.3.6 trillion budget for the 2021/2022 financial year that starts on 1st July 2021 and asked parliament to support the budget by increasing the public debt ceiling above the current ksh.9 trillion. But even before parliament considers Yatani&rsquo;s proposal, two rights activists have moved to court seeking the 2021/2022 budget declared unconstitutional because of exceeding the mandatory limit set by parliament in the budget policy statement by ksh.608 billion. Our senior parliament reporter Patrick Amimo examines the budget numbers that appear not to be adding up
